{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:proverbs.18",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 18,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 18 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:1",
      "text": "Through desire a man, having separated himself, seeketh and intermeddleth with all wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:2",
      "text": "A fool hath no delight in understanding, but that his heart may discover itself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:3",
      "text": "When the wicked cometh, then cometh also contempt, and with ignominy reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:4",
      "text": "The words of a man’s mouth are as deep waters, and the wellspring of wisdom as a flowing brook.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:5",
      "text": "It is not good to accept the person of the wicked, to overthrow the righteous in judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:6",
      "text": "A fool’s lips enter into contention, and his mouth calleth for strokes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:7",
      "text": "A fool’s mouth is his destruction, and his lips are the snare of his soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:8",
      "text": "The words of a talebearer are as wounds, and they go down into the innermost parts of the belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:9",
      "text": "He also that is slothful in his work is brother to him that is a great waster.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:10",
      "text": "The name of the Lord is a strong tower: the righteous runneth into it, and is safe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:11",
      "text": "The rich man’s wealth is his strong city, and as an high wall in his own conceit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:12",
      "text": "Before destruction the heart of man is haughty, and before honour is humility.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:13",
      "text": "He that answereth a matter before he heareth it, it is folly and shame unto him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:14",
      "text": "The spirit of a man will sustain his infirmity; but a wounded spirit who can bear?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:15",
      "text": "The heart of the prudent getteth knowledge; and the ear of the wise seeketh knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:16",
      "text": "A man’s gift maketh room for him, and bringeth him before great men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:17",
      "text": "He that is first in his own cause seemeth just; but his neighbour cometh and searcheth him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:18",
      "text": "The lot causeth contentions to cease, and parteth between the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:19",
      "text": "A brother offended is harder to be won than a strong city: and their contentions are like the bars of a castle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:20",
      "text": "A man’s belly shall be satisfied with the fruit of his mouth; and with the increase of his lips shall he be filled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:21",
      "text": "Death and life are in the power of the tongue: and they that love it shall eat the fruit thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:22",
      "text": "Whoso findeth a wife findeth a good thing, and obtaineth favour of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:23",
      "text": "The poor useth intreaties; but the rich answereth roughly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.18.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:24",
      "text": "A man that hath friends must shew himself friendly: and there is a friend that sticketh closer than a brother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
